title: High school sports roundup
text:

VOLLEYBALL 
Division III Sectional 
Highland 3, Mount Gilead 0 
Highland (21-2) defeated Mount Gilead in three sets (25-9, 25-13, 25-12) in Division III sectional semifinal action on Tuesday. Brogin Denman had 13 kills and five aces for Highland, Taylor Belcher had 11 aces and 10 assists, Jorden Goodman had 15 assists, Marlese Ferguson had 11 assists; and Bridget Oder had 15 digs. 
Highland hosts Liberty Union at 6 p.m. Thursday in a sectional final. 
Elgin 3, Worthington Christian 0 
Elgin downed Worthington Christian (25-23, 25-16, 25-16) Tuesday to move into Saturday’s 2:30 p.m. sectional final match at North Union. 
Miranda Haas secured 12 points and 17 assists for Elgin (15-8). Brianna Appelfeller tallied 10 points and nine digs; Kadi Vermillion produced eight points, two aces and 12 assists; Meridith Cocherl smacked 11 kills and three blocks; Tailor Wolf slugged 11 kills; and Alyssa Rankin received 15 of 15. 
Pleasant 3, CSG 0 
Pleasant advanced to a sectional final by beating Columbus School for Girls 25-14, 25-13, 25-12 on Tuesday. 
Pleasant will host Fredericktown at 6 p.m. Thursday in the sectional final. 
Fairbanks 3, Northmor 1 
Northmor (12-10) lost to Fairbanks in four sets (17-25, 25-23, 18-25, 21-25) in Division III sectional semifinal action on Tuesday. Jordan Zoll had 23 assists and two aces for Northmor, Anna Donner had 14 kills, Kelsie Fike had two aces, Karlee Carroll had 15 digs while Mikayla Briggs and Hope Miracle each had one block. 
Utica 3, Cardington-Lincoln 1 
Cardington-Lincoln’s season came to an end Tuesday with a 25-20, 24-26, 14-25, 7-25 loss to Utica in Div. III. 
Samantha Brininger contributed eight kills and 18 digs for Cardington-Lincoln. Haden Hursey and Jordan Deskins each added eight kills, Marissa Hall dished 29 assists, and Rylie Partlow had 19 digs. 
Ready 3, Centerburg 0 
Centerburg was bounced 20-25, 24-26, 14-25 by Bishop Ready in Div. III play. 
Renee Lemke accounted for 17 assists, nine digs and five points for Centerburg.
